# SHROUD Tor configuration (example)
# =====================================
# Drop into /etc/tor/torrc.d/shroud.conf and restart tor.
# See docs/tor.md for the full deployment guide.

# --- Hidden service for the SHROUD server ---------------------------------
# This publishes a v3 onion address that maps to the locally-bound server.
# The matching server invocation is:
#   python -m server.server --bind 127.0.0.1
HiddenServiceDir /var/lib/tor/shroud/
HiddenServicePort 58443 127.0.0.1:58443
HiddenServiceVersion 3

# Optional: rate-limit and harden the hidden service.
# HiddenServiceNonAnonymousMode 0
# HiddenServiceSingleHopMode 0
# HiddenServiceEnableIntroDoSDefense 1

# --- SOCKS for local clients (uncomment ONE) ---------------------------------
# Standalone tor daemon: keep the default 9050.
# SocksPort 127.0.0.1:9050

# Co-existing with Tor Browser, which binds 9150 — pick a non-clashing port.
# SocksPort 127.0.0.1:9051

# --- Logs --------------------------------------------------------------------
# Quiet but not silent. Set to debug only when troubleshooting onion bringup.
Log notice file /var/log/tor/notices.log
